[[Category:Tennis records and statistics|p]]

{{main|Grammy Award}} [[Image:Staples Center, LA, CA, jjron 22.03.2012.jpg|thumb|250px|right|upright|alt=|The [[Staples Center]] in [[Los Angeles]] is the current home of the Grammy Awards and has hosted seventeen times]]
The Grammy Awards have been held in many prestigious locations. In 1971 the Grammy Awards had its first live telecast and therefore had its own sole venue each year for the telecast. From 1963 to 1970 the Academy aired a TV special annually called "The Best On Record" which highlighted the awards dinners. Since 2000, the Grammy Awards have been held in the [[Staples Center]] located in [[Downtown Los Angeles]].
==Non-televised era== From 1959 to 1970 Awards dinners were held in the following locations simultaneously on the same day: *1959–1961: [[Los Angeles]] and [[New York City|New York]] *1962–1964: [[Chicago]], Los Angeles and New York *1965–1970: Chicago, Los Angeles, [[Nashville]] and New York
==Televised era== [[Image:Hollywood Palladium.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=|The [[Hollywood Palladium]], four-time ceremony site, in 2005]] [[Image:Gershwin Theatre NYC.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=|Uris Theatre (now known as [[Gershwin Theatre]]), in 2007]] [[Image:Shrine Auditorium.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=|Sixteen-time Grammy venue [[Shrine Auditorium]], in 2004]] [[Image:Radio City Music Hall Panorama.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=|[[Radio City Music Hall]], a five-time ceremony venue, in 2010]] [[Image:Madisonsquaregarden.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=|[[Madison Square Garden]], a three time ceremony venue, in 2003]]
Grammy Award ceremonies have been televised since 1971. The [[Staples Center]] has hosted the most Grammy telecasts, having hosted seventeen times. The [[Shrine Auditorium]] which hosted sixteen times was surpassed by the Staples Center in 2017. Los Angeles has held a total of 36 Grammy Award telecasts, with New York having hosted nine times and Nashville serving as host once.
